node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWS HOCKEY COLLECTIVE DAVID KREJCI ANNOUNCES HE'S LEAVING THE BRUINS TO RETURN TO CZECH REPUBLIC H/T: BOSTON BRUINS'.

node.text: David Krejci will not be returning to the Boston Bruins.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWS HOCKEY COLLECTIVE DAVID KREJCI ANNOUNCES HE'S LEAVING THE BRUINS TO RETURN TO CZECH REPUBLIC H/T: BOSTON BRUINS'.

Photo by Hockey Collective on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Bank n CCM In January of 2007 when pulled the Black and Gold sweater on for the first time was 20 years old and was almost 4,000 miles away from home. BaueR Since then, you have embraced me as Bostonian. have given everything that have had to you and the Bruins, and over time, Boston has become a second home to me. met my amazing wife Naomi here, and our two beautiful children call Boston home. This City and your support are so special to me. 46 DAVID KREJCI'.

Photo by Hockey Collective on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '46 CCM " The Bruins organizațion has always treated me with the utmost respect. am so thankful for my teammates, the trainers and support staff; coaches and management who have allowed me to be part of so many great teams. Obviously the 2011, 2013 and 2019 teams stick out, but truthfully have loved every Bruins team have been a part of. 46 DAVID KREJCI'.

Photo by Hockey Collective on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'CCM Since the end of the season as have thought about my future, has become clear that need to make a difficult decision for my family and At this point in my career and life need to return to the Czech Republic and play in front of my family who sacrificed so much to help me achieve my NHL dreams. want to play in front of my parents, brother and friends. want my children to live where grew up, spend time with so many Czech family members who love them and create lifelong memories 46 DAVID KREJCI B'.

Photo by Hockey Collective on July 30, 2021. May be an image of text that says '46 KREJCI adidas So for now, want to thank all the Bruins fans for the support they have shown my family and over the last 14 years. will forever be thankful. Thisis not goodbye, will not be a stranger. will be Bruin forever. will see you at the TD Garden soon, and will always bleed Black and Gold. With gratitude, David 46 DAVID KREJCI'.

node.text: Zach Werenski makes more money than Cale Makar.

node.text: Ryan Reaves is headed to the Rangers. The pick is a 2022 3rd rounder.

node.text: Brandon Saad is headed to the St. Louis Blues on a five-year deal.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on July 29, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '194 A BBUBR SIGNED COREY PERRY Yanea UER 2 YEARS, $2M ($1M AAV) HOCKEY COLLECTIVE'.

node.text: If you can’t beat them, join them. Corey Perry is off to Tampa on a two-year deal.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'TRADE COL COLR RECEIVES .DARCY KUEMPER å 25 ARI RECEIVES •2022 1ST RD PICK •CONOR TIMMINS CRAIG MORGAN HOCKEY COLLECTIVE'.

node.text: Colorado finds their new starting goaltender, acquiring Darcy Kuemper from Arizona.

node.text: Pius Suter finds a suitor in the Detroit Red Wings.

node.text: Linus Ullmark signs a big four-year deal with the Bruins.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Hockey Collective on July 28, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'hard SIGNED BaUeR DOUGIE HAMILTON 19 7 YEARS, $63M ($9M AAV) HOCKEY COLLECTIVE'.

node.text: Dougie Hamilton has signed a seven-year deal with the New Jersey Devils.
